# Linting & Formatting

Biome is the single tool for both linting and formatting. Do not add ESLint or Prettier.

## Config (biome.json)

- 2-space indentation, 120 char line width
- Single quotes (JS), double quotes (JSX attributes)
- Recommended lint rules enabled
- Import organization enabled (auto-sorted by Biome)
- Ignored: `books_data.json`, `metadata.json`, `dist/**`, `public/assets/**`

## Commands

- `npm run lint` — check only (CI-friendly)
- `npm run lint:fix` — check + auto-fix
- `npm run format` — format only

## Pre-commit

Husky + lint-staged runs `biome check --write` on staged files automatically before every commit.

## Code Style Enforced

- No unused imports or variables.
- `import type` for type-only imports.
- No `any` — use specific types.
- Semicolons required.
- Trailing commas in multi-line structures.
